description: Submits profiling data to an aggregated profile of a profiling group. To get an aggregated profile that is created with this profiling data, use GetProfile.

parameters.name: contentType
parameters.description:
The format of the submitted profiling data. The format maps to the Accept and Content-Type headers of the HTTP request. You can specify one of the following: or the default . ``

  • application/json -- standard JSON format

  • application/x-amzn-ion -- the Amazon Ion data format. For more information, see Amazon Ion.

``

parameters.name: profileToken
parameters.description: Amazon CodeGuru Profiler uses this universally unique identifier (UUID) to prevent the accidental submission of duplicate profiling data if there are failures and retries. This field is autopopulated if not provided.

parameters.name: profilingGroupName
parameters.description: The name of the profiling group with the aggregated profile that receives the submitted profiling data.
